	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Action</strong> - Self - 6th Level (Abjuration) - VSM (a statuette of yourself worth 1,500 gp) - 10 Days</p><p><strong>Utility</strong></p><ul><li><p>Choose a spell of 5th level or lower that you can cast, that has a casting time of 1 action, and that can target only you. Cast that spell as part of casting <em>Contingency</em>, expending both spell slots. The chosen spell takes effect only when a triggering circumstance occurs.</p></li><li><p><strong>Trigger: </strong>You describe the condition under which the chosen spell takes effect. The spell is cast instantly when the condition is met, even if you are &amp;reference[unconscious apply=false]. The spell cast doesn't require &amp;reference[Concentration] even if it normally would.</p></li><li><p><strong>Limitation: </strong>You can have only one <em>Contingency</em> spell active at a time. If you cast <em>Contingency</em> again, the previous one ends. <em>Contingency</em> ends if the material the statuette is ever destroyed.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
